/&gt;<![CDATA[France has approved a nationwide ban on social media for children under fifteen. This new law also prohibits mobile phone use within high schools across the nation. President Macron wants the ban to begin at the start of the next school year. This measure aims to protect young users from harmful online content and its effects. Several other European countries are also considering similar restrictions on digital platforms.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/france-lawmakers-pass-law-banning-social-media-for-children-under-15-first-eu-nation-to-do-so/articleshow/132548839.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/france-lawmakers-pass-law-banning-social-media-for-children-under-15-first-eu-nation-to-do-so/articleshow/132548839.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-22T04:11:25+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132548840,imgsize-521824.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[IShowSpeed's Instagram Reel featuring BTS becomes most-viewed in first 24 hours with 300 million views]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132546605.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[IShowSpeed's Instagram Reel of meeting BTS at the FIFA World Cup 2026 final achieved a record. The viral video garnered an impressive 300 million views within its initial twenty-four hours. This encounter brought together a major streamer and a popular K-pop group, creating significant buzz. Fans worldwide rapidly shared the clip, contributing to its immense popularity and viral spread.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/ishowspeeds-instagram-reel-featuring-bts-becomes-most-viewed-in-first-24-hours-with-300-million-views/articleshow/132546605.cms]]></link>