usands of centrifuges to Pickaxe Mountain - Report]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132542730.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/israel-says-iran-moved-thousands-of-centrifuges-to-pickaxe-mountain-report/articleshow/132542730.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/israel-says-iran-moved-thousands-of-centrifuges-to-pickaxe-mountain-report/articleshow/132542730.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-21T22:56:57+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132543427,imgsize-286122.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA['Are you the only Indian hire?' AI engineer denied B1 visa for company offsite, Redditors point out he has to prove why the meeting can't be held online]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132541282.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/are-you-the-only-indian-hire-ai-engineer-denied-b1-visa-for-company-offsite-redditors-point-out-he-has-to-prove-why-the-meeting-cant-be-held-online/articleshow/132541282.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/are-you-the-only-indian-hire-ai-engineer-denied-b1-visa-for-company-offsite-redditors-point-out-he-has-to-prove-why-the-meeting-cant-be-held-online/articleshow/132541282.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-21T21:37:06+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132541289,imgsize-168080.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Scientists studying bee brains found how colonies coordinate without a central controller]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132534955.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Honeybee colonies organise work without any leader assigning tasks, but scientists have now discovered that specific brain circuits help control this process. By changing the activity of a gene-linked neural circuit, researchers made older worker bees return to caring for the queen, a job usually done only by younger bees. The findings offer new insight into how bees coordinate complex social behaviour.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/scientists-studying-bee-brains-found-clues-to-how-colonies-coordinate-complex-behaviour-without-a-central-controller-relying-instead-on-many-small-individual-decisions/articleshow/132534955.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/scientists-studying-bee-brains-found-clues-to-how-colonies-coordinate-complex-behaviour-without-a-central-controller-relying-instead-on-many-small-individual-decisions/articleshow/132534955.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-21T22:00:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132538708,imgsize-313438.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Ex-UK minister Ann Widdecombe was hit 21 times with hammer as she ate lunch, court told]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132543459.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/ex-uk-minister-ann-widdecombe-was-hit-21-times-with-hammer-as-she-ate-lunch-court-told/articleshow/132543459.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/ex-uk-minister-ann-widdecombe-was-hit-21-times-with-hammer-as-she-ate-lunch-court-told/articleshow/132543459.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-21T23:01:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132543471,imgsize-70900.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[What does it really take to become an astronaut for NASA and who can apply for it?]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132532372.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[The selection process for astronauts at NASA is rigorous and far more demanding than academic qualifications alone. Candidates undergo psychological testing and participate in team-based simulations that are designed to push them to their limits. Psychologists purposefully create high-pressure situations to gauge how well candidates maintain composure and teamwork. This comprehensive method ensures that only the most adaptable individuals are chosen for space missions.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/six-hours-of-psychological-testing-three-hours-of-behavioural-interview-what-does-it-really-take-to-become-an-astronaut-for-nasa-and-who-can-apply-for-it/articleshow/132532372.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/six-hours-of-psychological-testing-three-hours-of-behavioural-interview-what-does-it-really-take-to-become-an-astronaut-for-nasa-and-who-can-apply-for-it/articleshow/132532372.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-21T21:00:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132532417,imgsize-144354.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[From gym to hangar to sleeping quarters: Iran's three-missile strikes on US base in Jordan]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132539836.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[An Iranian missile attack tragically claimed the lives of  US service members at a Jordanian air base, targeting their sleeping quarters. This shocking incident exposed critical shortcomings in the protection of American forces. Following the strike, US President Donald Trump committed to retaliation, while Iran's supreme leader issued a stark warning about consequences for continued aggression.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/from-gym-to-hangar-to-sleeping-quarters-irans-three-missile-strikes-on-us-base-in-jordan/articleshow/132539836.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/from-gym-to-hangar-to-sleeping-quarters-irans-three-missile-strikes-on-us-base-in-jordan/articleshow/132539836.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-21T20:30:05+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132539914,imgsize-27620.cms"/></item></channel></rss>